  </div>
  <div>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">What size solar system do I need in North Carolina?</h3>
    <p>The average North Carolina home uses approximately 10,000-12,000 kWh of electricity annually, requiring a 6-8kW solar system for complete energy offset. System sizing depends on your specific electricity usage, roof space and orientation, shading conditions, and energy goals. A properly sized system in North Carolina generates about 1,300-1,400 kWh per installed kilowatt annually. Homes with electric heat pumps, electric vehicles, or pools typically require larger systems. Solar installers use 12 months of utility bills, roof measurements, and shading analysis to determine optimal system size. Most homeowners choose to offset 80-100% of their electricity usage, though larger systems may be beneficial for homes planning to add electric vehicles or other high-energy appliances.</p>
